BT 1 0 0 1 30 531.6756 Tm  T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 30 523.2756 Tm (      1. Executive Summary) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 30 514.8756 Tm (      Investigation INV-2022-0045 was initiated following observation of a gradual upward trend in S1 calibration signal for) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 30 506.4756 Tm (      NEXUS CK MB lots manufactured between August and September 2022. Three consecutive lots \(1009900820,) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 30 498.0756 Tm (      1009900821, 1009900822\) showed S1 values above 530 SIU, approaching the upper specification limit of 550 SIU.) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 30 489.6756 Tm (      No lots exceeded specifications, but the trend warranted investigation per SOP-QA-010.) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 30 481.2756 Tm (      The investigation determined that the root cause was gradual wear of the optical sensor on calibration station) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 30 472.8756 Tm (      EQ-CAL-001, resulting in a systematic positive bias in fluorescence readings. The issue was resolved through) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 30 464.4756 Tm (      preventive maintenance \(sensor replacement\) and enhanced trend monitoring was implemented.) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 30 456.0756 Tm  T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 30 447.6756 Tm  T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 30 439.2756 Tm  T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 30 430.8756 Tm  T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 30 422.4756 Tm (      2. Problem Description \(QQOCQPC\)) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 30 414.0756 Tm  T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 30 405.6756 Tm (      Qui \(Who\):) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 30 397.2756 Tm (      QC laboratory team \(analysts QC-002, QC-003\) performing routine calibration verification on NEXUS CK MB) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 30 388.8756 Tm (      production lots.) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 30 380.4756 Tm  T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 30 372.0756 Tm  T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 30 363.6756 Tm (      Quoi \(What\):) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 30 355.2756 Tm (      Gradual upward drift in S1 calibration signal values. S1 readings increased from typical 500 SIU to 530-540 SIU over) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 30 346.8756 Tm (      a 6-week period.) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 30 338.4756 Tm  T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 30 330.0756 Tm  T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 30 321.6756 Tm (      Ou \(Where\):) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 30 313.2756 Tm (      Calibration station EQ-CAL-001 at Riverside production facility, QC laboratory area B.) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 30 304.8756 Tm  T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 30 296.4756 Tm  T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 30 288.0756 Tm (      Comment \(How\):) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 30 279.6756 Tm (      Trend identified during routine SPC chart review. S1 values showed consistent upward trend across consecutive lots) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 30 271.2756 Tm (      while S2 remained stable.) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 30 262.8756 Tm  T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 30 254.4756 Tm  T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 30 246.0756 Tm (      Quand \(When\):) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 30 237.6756 Tm (      Trend first observed: August 2022. Investigation opened: 2022-09-15 after third consecutive lot above 530 SIU.) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 30 229.2756 Tm  T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 30 220.8756 Tm  T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 30 212.4756 Tm (      Pourquoi \(Why\):) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 30 204.0756 Tm (      Equipment aging - optical sensor degradation causing increased fluorescence readings. Normal wear pattern, but PM) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 30 195.6756 Tm (      interval was insufficient to prevent measurable drift.) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 30 187.2756 Tm  T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 30 178.8756 Tm  T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 30 170.4756 Tm (      Combien \(How much\):) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 30 162.0756 Tm (      3 lots affected \(1009900820-1009900822\). No OOS results. No product impact - all lots released within specification.) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 30 153.6756 Tm (      Estimated cost: 2,500 EUR \(investigation + PM acceleration\).) Tj T* ET
